+# GSG: Build and Validation Guide for OpenVINO GPU Plugin Custom Ops
+
+This guide explains how to build OpenVINO and validate that the BEVFusion custom operators (SparseConvolution, SparseToDense, BevPoolV2) run correctly in the Intel GPU plugin.
+
+## 1. Build OpenVINO (Release + Tests)
+
+> **Compiler matters**: the SparseConvolution / SparseToDense / BevPoolV2
+> GPU-plugin implementations live in SYCL source files. The `OV_GPU_WITH_SYCL`
+> CMake flag only gets turned on when `CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER` is an Intel oneAPI
+> compiler (`icpx`). If you forget to `source /opt/intel/oneapi/setvars.sh`
+> first, CMake falls back to the system `gcc`/`g++`, the SYCL impls are
+> silently dropped from `libopenvino_intel_gpu_plugin.so`, and at model load
+> time you will see errors like:
+>
+> ```
+> No conversion rule found for operations: org.openvinotoolkit.SparseConvolution, org.openvinotoolkit.SparseToDense
+> ```
+>
+> (This also happens if one build used gcc and a later incremental build
+> sourced setvars — the CMakeCache still pins the old compiler. When in doubt
+> `rm -rf build` and reconfigure.)
+
+### 1.1 Preferred: use the `icpx` wrapper scripts
+
+Two wrapper scripts handle the `source setvars.sh` + compiler selection in one
+go. They are the standard way to build this tree:
+
+```bash
+cd openvino
+
+# Clean reconfigure with icx/icpx — writes full log to configure_icpx.log.
+# Does `source /opt/intel/oneapi/setvars.sh --force`, exports CC=icx / CXX=icpx,
+# and runs `cmake -S . -B build` with -DCMAKE_CXX_COMPILER=icpx,
+# -DENABLE_TESTS=ON, -DENABLE_PYTHON_API=ON, -DENABLE_ONEDNN_FOR_GPU=ON.
+bash configure_icpx.sh 2>&1 | tee configure_icpx.log
+
+# Build — writes full log to build_icpx.log. Re-sources setvars.sh so SYCL
+# headers / libraries are on the path, then runs `cmake --build build -j$(nproc)`.
+bash build_icpx.sh 2>&1 | tee build_icpx.log
+```
+
+Why two scripts instead of one: `configure_icpx.sh` only needs to run when
+`CMakeCache.txt` is missing or you intentionally want to re-run CMake; day to
+day incremental builds just need `build_icpx.sh` (or a plain
+`cmake --build build` if the shell already has oneAPI sourced).
+
+### 1.2 Manual build (no wrapper)
+
+If you want to do it by hand, remember to `source` oneAPI first:
+
+```bash
+cd openvino
+git submodule update --init --recursive
+source /opt/intel/oneapi/setvars.sh --force       # <-- must, otherwise gcc is used
+rm -rf build bin                                   # only on first configure
+cmake -S . -B build \
+    -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \
+    -DCMAKE_C_COMPILER=icx \
+    -DCMAKE_CXX_COMPILER=icpx \
+    -DENABLE_TESTS=ON \
+    -DENABLE_PYTHON_API=ON \
+    -DENABLE_ONEDNN_FOR_GPU=ON
+cmake --build build -j"$(nproc)"
+```
+
+Expected result:
+- Build completes successfully.
+- Test binaries are generated under `bin/intel64/Release`.
+- Python bindings are generated under `bin/intel64/Release/python`.
+- `libopenvino_intel_gpu_plugin.so` contains the SYCL implementations; ONNX
+  frontend recognizes `org.openvinotoolkit.SparseConvolution`,
+  `org.openvinotoolkit.SparseToDense`, and `org.openvinotoolkit.BevPoolV2`.
+
+Quick check the compiler CMake actually picked:
+
+```bash
+grep CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER:FILEPATH build/CMakeCache.txt
+# Must show: .../oneapi/compiler/.../bin/icpx  (NOT /usr/bin/c++ or gcc)
+```
+
+### 1.3 Incremental build (after code changes)
+
+For targeted rebuilds after modifying specific components:
+
+```bash
+# GPU plugin only (SparseConvolution/SparseToDense SYCL kernels, BevPoolV2 OCL kernels)
+cmake --build build -j"$(nproc)" --target openvino_intel_gpu_plugin
+
+# ONNX frontend only (ONNX attribute parsing changes)
+cmake --build build -j"$(nproc)" --target openvino_onnx_frontend
+
+# Python bindings (required when commit hash changes)
+cmake --build build -j"$(nproc)" --target pyopenvino
+```
+
+**Important**: SparseConvolution and SparseToDense span both ONNX frontend and GPU plugin.
+If you modify ONNX frontend source files, you must rebuild **both** `openvino_onnx_frontend`
+and `openvino_intel_gpu_plugin` targets. Building only one will cause version mismatches or
+stale attribute parsing.
+
+> For incremental builds, either run `bash build_icpx.sh` (it re-sources oneAPI
+> for you) or make sure the current shell has already sourced
+> `/opt/intel/oneapi/setvars.sh`.
+
+## 2. BevPoolV2 Test Matrix (Core + GPU + Frontend)
+
+Build test binaries and runtime model zoo assets first:
+
+```bash
+cd openvino
+cmake --build build \
+  --target ov_core_unit_tests ov_gpu_unit_tests ov_gpu_func_tests ov_onnx_frontend_tests test_model_zoo \
+  --parallel 8
+```
+
+Run focused BevPoolV2 tests:
+
+```bash
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_core_unit_tests --gtest_filter='*BevPoolV2*'
+
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_gpu_unit_tests --gtest_filter='*BevPoolV2*'
+
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_gpu_func_tests --gtest_filter='*BevPoolV2*'
+
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_onnx_frontend_tests --gtest_filter='*onnx_model_bevpool*'
+```
+
+Expected result:
+- All selected tests are discovered and pass.
+
+If no tests are shown:
+- Check test registration and filter string.
+- For `ov_gpu_unit_tests`, remember gtest filtering is case-sensitive.
+- To inspect names, run:
+
+```bash
+./bin/intel64/Release/ov_gpu_unit_tests --gtest_list_tests | grep -i bevpool
+```
+
+### 2.1 ONNX frontend test prerequisites
+
+`ov_onnx_frontend_tests` relies on runtime models under:
+
+- `bin/intel64/Release/test_model_zoo`
+
+If Python ONNX requirements are not installed in your environment, the current CMake fallback converts ONNX text `.prototxt` to binary ModelProto via `protoc`, so the BevPoolV2 ONNX frontend tests can still run.
+
+### 2.2 Accuracy acceptance thresholds (P1/P3 baseline)
+
+Use the following thresholds for BevPoolV2 correctness acceptance:
+
+- f32 baseline path: abs <= 1e-4, rel <= 1e-4
+- f32 stress shapes with very large accumulation (for example M >= 300000): abs <= 3e-3, rel <= 3e-3
+- f16 path: abs <= 2e-3, rel <= 2e-3
+
+Rationale:
+- f16 path may include mixed-precision accumulation/rounding effects.
+- f32 path keeps a tighter bound to catch silent drift before optimization changes.
+
