+### 3.2 Per-layer validation (21 layers, spconv reference)
+
+Validates each of the 21 SparseEncoder layers individually against spconv reference data.
+Each layer is built as a standalone ONNX model, run through OpenVINO GPU inference in FP16,
+and compared against the spconv dump (voxel set match + feature tolerance).
+
+**Prerequisites**:
+- spconv reference dump: `test_data/sparse_conv_dump/` (21 npz files + manifest.json)
+- Python OpenVINO bindings built from source (Section 1)
+- Python venv at `/home/jie/env/spconvEnv/`
+
+The wrapper [`run_validation.sh`](run_validation.sh) pre-sets `PYTHONPATH` and
+`LD_LIBRARY_PATH` to the locally built OpenVINO under `bin/intel64/Release` so the
+SparseConvolution / SparseToDense ONNX translators are picked up (the pip-installed
+`openvino` package does not have them).
+
+```bash
+cd openvino
+./run_validation.sh                    # all 21 layers
+./run_validation.sh --layers 0,5,20    # specific layers only
+./run_validation.sh --fp32             # FP32 precision
+```
+
+The wrapper hard-codes the interpreter and dump dir; change them there if your
+layout differs:
+
+```bash
+PYTHON="/home/jie/env/spconvEnv/bin/python"
+DUMP_DIR="$SCRIPT_DIR/test_data/sparse_conv_dump"
+```
+
+Manual invocation (equivalent, useful for debugging):
+
+```bash
+OV_DIR=/home/jie/workspace/openvino/bin/intel64/Release \
+    PYTHONPATH="$OV_DIR/python:$PYTHONPATH" \
+    LD_LIBRARY_PATH="$OV_DIR:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH" \
+    /home/jie/env/spconvEnv/bin/python test_sparse_encoder_validation.py \
+    --dump-dir /home/jie/workspace/openvino/test_data/sparse_conv_dump
