+### 3.4 ONNX model export (requires mmdet3d environment)
+
+To re-export the ONNX model after weight ordering or attribute changes:
+
+```bash
+# In the mmdet3d conda/venv environment (NOT the OpenVINO build environment)
+cd bevfusion
+python export/export_sparse_encoder_onnx.py \
+    configs/nuscenes/det/transfusion/secfpn/camera+lidar/swint_v0p075/convfuser.yaml \
+    pretrained/bevfusion-det.pth \
+    -o ../openvino/test_data/sparse_encoder_new.onnx \
+    --output-bound 80000
+```
+
+Key points:
+- Weights are stored in ix-major order matching spconv convention: `[kx,ky,kz,Cin,Cout]` → `reshape(K,Cin,Cout)` (no permutation needed)
+- `--output-bound 80000` is required for SparseConv3d stride>1 buffer pre-allocation
+- BN is fused into conv weight & bias; ReLU is fused as `activation="ReLU"` attribute
+
