+## 4. ONNX Runtime Validation with benchmark_app
+
+### 4.1 SparseConvolution + SparseToDense (SparseEncoder)
+
+**Note**: benchmark_app uses random input by default. For SparseConvolution, random int32
+coordinates in a large spatial space produce near-empty kernel maps, giving unrealistically
+low latency. Always use real voxel data for meaningful benchmarks.
+
+```bash
+cd openvino
+
+# Export real input data (one-time) — already checked into test_data/
+python3 -c "
+import numpy as np
+d = np.load('/home/jie/workspace/openvino/test_data/sparse_encoder_dump/module_encoders_lidar_backbone_SparseEncoder.npz')
+np.save('test_data/e2e_features.npy', d['voxel_features'].astype(np.float32))
+np.save('test_data/e2e_indices.npy', d['coors'].astype(np.int32))
+"
+
+# Real data benchmark (recommended)
+./bin/intel64/Release/benchmark_app \
+    -m test_data/sparse_encoder_new.onnx -d GPU -niter 20 -hint latency \
+    -shape "features[36294,4],indices[36294,4]" \
+    -i features:test_data/e2e_features.npy \
+    -i indices:test_data/e2e_indices.npy
+```
+
